# "Snapped scrolled content" tests:
# These tests check the following: No matter how you scroll, the scrolled contents should
# always be rendered with the same snapping as if you hadn't scrolled; there should not
# be any subpixel "shimmers" during scrolling. In other words, the device pixel
# rendering at scroll position zero and the device pixel rendering at any other scroll
# position should be identical except for an integer device pixel translation of the contents.
# The zoom tests are marked with fails-if(useDrawSnapshot) due to bug 1917424.
